\prod_{k=1}^\infty1 - \frac{1}{(p_k)^2} = \frac{6}{\pi^2}
\prod_{k=1}^\infty\frac{{p_k}^2}{{p_k}^2 - 1} = \frac{\pi^2}{6}
\prod_{k=1}^\infty \frac{1}{1-1/p_k^2} = \prod_{k=1}^\infty \sum_{j=0}^\infty \frac1{p_k^j}.
\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac1{n^2} = \frac{\pi^2}6.
\zeta(2)
\zeta(2) = \frac{\pi^2}{6}
